  <prompt>
    In `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/main.tsx`, invoke the Daily Briefing registration factory with `loadNotificationContext: loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` alongside the existing `setDefaultWorkspaceRenderer` call. After this change, cold-load of the SpaarkeAi workspace pane MUST populate Daily Briefing with TL;DR + non-empty channel bullets for users with N&gt;0 unread `appnotification` rows.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in SpaarkeAi workspace bootstrap, LegalWorkspace section registration, and the `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` helper.</role>

  <goal>SpaarkeAi `main.tsx` injects `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` into the Daily Briefing section registration factory; cold-load of the workspace pane renders real notifications for `ralph.schroeder@spaarke.com` (or any user with unread rows) in spaarkedev1.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-02 and design.md §D1: `loadSpaarkeAiNotificationContext` already exists but is orphaned (no caller wires it through to BFF `/narrate`). Task 001 added the factory option; this task wires the actual injection.
    </background>
